•''China: Through the Looking Glass'' is the most visited exhibition in the Center's history with 815,992 visitors (fifth most visited in the Museum's history). ''Alexander McQueen: Savage Beauty'' is the second most visited with 661,509 visitors (ninth most visited in the Museum's History).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.artnews.com/2015/09/12/a-look-at-the-mets-top-ten-most-visited-exhibitions-of-all-time/|title=A Look at the Met's Top 10 Most Visited Exhibitions of All Time|last=Greenberger|first=Alex|date=2015-09-12|website=ARTnews|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180720051839/http://www.artnews.com/2015/09/12/a-look-at-the-mets-top-ten-most-visited-exhibitions-of-all-time/|archive-date=20 July 2018|dead-url=|access-date=2019-01-29}}</ref>

